### Description

I followed the the guide about [ApplicationRef#is-stable-examples](https://angular.io/api/core/ApplicationRef#is-stable-examples). When i tried to delete the pipe like this, and the console.log executed endless until the browser crushed.

```
constructor(appRef: ApplicationRef), zone: NgZone)) {
  appRef.isStable.subscribe(state => zone.run(() => {
    console.log('endless call');
    // You don't want to do this
    ngZone.run(() => (this.value = state));
  }));
}
```

It is horrible to misuse it. Maybe `ApplicationRef`, `ngZone` or `zone.js` could take some protection to avoid this.  
Or at least, adding a warning in the doc.


